gw.plugin.account

Interface IAccountPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface IAccountPlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin
    External account plugin interface. Contains methods for detecting existing accounts, performing name clearance, generating account numbers, and doing risk reservation.

      • isRiskReserved

        boolean isRiskReserved(PolicyPeriod period)
                throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Checks whether the given PolicyPeriod is already risk reserved. If a PolicyPeriod is reserved, then a new submission with that period will not be bindable in PolicyCenter.
        Parameters:
        period - PolicyPeriod to check for risk reservation
        Returns:
        true if the PolicyPeriod is reserved, false otherwise
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if a communication-related exception occurs

      • transferPolicies

        void transferPolicies(Policy[] policies,
                      Account fromAccount,
                      Account toAccount)
               throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Called after the passed in Policies have been transferred from fromAccount to toAccount. At this point any additional transfer logic can be performed, including account transfer on external systems.

        Note, the method Account.transferPolicies(Policy[], Account) is responsible for actually moving the core items such as Policies, Notes, and Activities.

        Parameters:
        policies - The policies to be transferred
        fromAccount - The source account
        toAccount - The destination account
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if a communication-related exception occurs
        See Also:
        Account.transferPolicies(entity.Policy[], entity.Account)

      • freezeAccount

        void freezeAccount(Account account)
            throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Called to signal that the passed-in Account is frozen because it is about to be deleted. Should alert any external systems synchronously to freeze their copies of the Account. A frozen Account must not allow Policies to be created on it.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to be frozen
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if a communication-related exception occurs

      • mergeAccounts

        void mergeAccounts(Account fromAccount,
                   Account toAccount)
            throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Called after two Accounts have been merged together in PolicyCenter, just before "fromAccount" is retired. At this point customer code should move any additional data from fromAccount to toAccount and synchronously tell any external systems to merge fromAccount into toAccount.
        Parameters:
        fromAccount - The account that will be merged and deleted
        toAccount - The account into which the "fromAccount" will be merged
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if a communication-related exception occurs

      • accountContactRoleDenormOptimization

        boolean accountContactRoleDenormOptimization()
        During an account merge, if the account contact roles have been changed, we will look through all the policy periods that have a Primary Insured as a conact on the account contact role, and ensure that they are properly denormed on the policy periods. During account merge by return true, we will only look at the policy periods in the fromAccount and the toAccount.
        Returns:
        true if only look at the policy periods in the from and to Account, false will continue existing behavior

      • checkCanMergeWithAccount

        java.lang.String checkCanMergeWithAccount(Account fromAccount,
                                          Account toAccount)
        Checks whether or not an account can be merged with another. This should be called prior to merging two accounts together. This method is included so that it can be overwritten and customized for a customer.
        Parameters:
        fromAccount - The account that will be merged and deleted
        toAccount - The account into which the "fromAccount" will be merged

      • isEditable

        java.lang.Boolean isEditable(Account account)
        Returns true if the specified account is editable. This method is included so that it can be overwritten and customized for a customer.
        Parameters:
        account - the Account to check editability on
        Returns:
        true if the Account is editable

      • populateAccountSummary

        void populateAccountSummary(AccountSummary summary,
                            Account account)
        Populates the extension fields on the AccountSummary with values from the the Account extension fields. This function should only change fields on the AccountSummary and will be called after the Account has been populated with values.
        Parameters:
        summary - The AccountSummary to be populated
        account - The Account from which the AccountSummary will be populated

      • getInverseRelationshipType

        AccountRelationshipType getInverseRelationshipType(AccountRelationshipType relationshipType)
        Returns the inverse of a given AccountRelationshipType, or the relationship type as viewed from the opposite direction. For instance the "parent of" and "child of" relationships are inverses of each other. It is also possible for a relationship to be its own inverse, such as "common ownership". This method should never return null.
        Parameters:
        relationshipType - the relationship type to inverse
        Returns:
        the inverse of the given relationship type
